<br>
Some advises i wanted to share :<br>
  - Phini : no comment, so much was already posted about it. It's an easy kill but uncommon drop for the BCS. I got it from the first kill, lucky I am !<br>
  - VS : enchanter with Rune 4/5 is ABSOLUTELY required to avoid VS life tap. I killed him a few times with m8, was always easy with an enchanter. Don't even try it without.<br>
  - BG : I had my alt drood at North wall during 1 month. BG is not trackable with a drood from North Wall but you can still check guild raids on PoF, check named like Dracoliche, Cazic... Sometimes i noticed the zone was empty... Well, i made my calculation upon the following and it worked : when the zone has been cleared, wait for Cazic or schissar to pop and organize your raid within the next 24 hours. BG should be up... Concerning the fight, it's tough because of potential adds that have not been cleared before the fight and because BG has a bunch of HP. My suggestion would be a minimum of 2 groupes with 1/2 enchanters, 2 cleric/CHdrood and a good tank as fundamental start.<br>
<br>
Good luck fellow wizards !<br>
